15/09/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Following intensive talks, three out of four trade unions in Romania's education sector finally agreed Tuesday (14 September) to sign an agreement with the government, enabling the smooth start of the new school year Wednesday. 
The cabinet and the unions have been negotiating for weeks on a proposed wage increase. 
The unions had threatened to launch protests if their request was not met. 
Only the Unions' Federation in Education refused to accept the deal.
In other news, Bucharest hosts a regional meeting Wednesday devoted to the fight against corruption in Southeast Europe (SEE). 
Experts from SEE countries and the Stability Pact for SEE are attending. 
(Rompres, Mediafax, AFP - 14/09/04)
